        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-03T23:52:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I assume that this comment applies equally well to images?  If so, move it above, and change the wording so its clear that it applies to all kinds of GLObjects that we keep track of.  (And I think this comment would be made even a little bit more clear if it added, after the second line \"-- which is why each process is mapped to a multiset of color buffer handles, rather than just a set.\")\n\nActually, maybe this comment doesn\u0027t apply to images -- I note that the map is from puid to Set\u003cImage\u003e, not MultiSet, as was the case for color buffers.  So I guess each image can get created only once per puid?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 819,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 821,
        "endChar": 71
      },
      "revId": "7bc701f8f502d74a9bc062a208cbb36c250a390d",
