    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d98d87b7_e0677cf5",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/host/libs/libOpenglRender/FrameBuffer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 1088,
      "author": {
        "id": 1087303
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-10T22:03:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would prefer waiting for the cleanup path - if there are a large number of guest processes, it will have other issues first. The memory usage here comparing to other process resources is insignificant.\n\nOn the other hand, a process can create and release one single EGLImage multiple times, which might have one extra allocation / deallocation if we erase m_procOwnedEGLImages[puid] (which is also insignificant comparing to other stuff).\n\nAll in all, I don\u0027t think we shall worry about this. what do you think?",
      "parentUuid": "54231e3a_7f7d8748",
